description: Arriving on a familiar looking space station, the Doctor, Amy, Rory, and new travelling companion Kevin - a cybernetic dinosaur - find a scientific crew under attack from a giant Cthulhloid space squid! With the security robot destoyed, it's up to the Doctor and his friends to save the day, but who will sacrifice themselves to save the many?
name: Space Squid

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: Finding themselves inside an alien asylum, the Doctor, Amy and Rory discover that many of the human patients within actually house the minds of some of the Doctor's most terrifying enemies. As the Doctor tries to work out who has doen this hideous body swap, the inmates riot and two characters will never be the same again.
name: Body Snatched: Part 1

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: This is the finale of the Body Snatchers story! The Doctor, Amy, and Rory find themselves in an alien asylum and make a startling discovery. Many of the asylum's human patients actually contain the minds of the Doctor's most terrifying enemies! Unfortunately, before the Doctor can deduce who has done this ghastly body swap, he falls victim!
name: Body Snatched: Part 2

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: A special, silent Christmas story that reunites writer Tony Lee with The Time Machination's Paul Grist! When robots attack Santa in order to destroy Christmas, it's up to the Doctor to save the day! But when one of Santa's reindeer is injured, can the TARDIS manage to get to everyone's house over Christmas Eve?
name: Silent Knight

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: Join the Doctor and friends in these four tantalizing tales: The Doctor tries to stay ahead of his pursuers in a topsy-turvy world in “Run, Doctor, Run” by Joshua Hale Fialkov and Blair Shedd. The Doctor discovers an alien warrior hiding in the English countryside in “Down to Earth” by Matthew Dow Smith and Mitch Gerads. Rory is the King of England. Amy is a revolutionary leader. The Doctor is a prisoner. Find out why in “Tuesday” by Dan McDaid. Fate and Fanaticism collide in “Your Destiny Awaits” by Tony Lee and Josh Adams.
name: Run, Doctor, Run; Down to Earth; Tuesday; Your Destiny Awaits

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

name: Les Tuniques Bleues : Une histoire canon !

description: Ahn-Ming climbs to the other side of the forbidden wall to learn that everything he's been taught about his evil neighbors is wrong.
name: The Forbidden City of Shenzhen

description:
Best Laid Plains

A formal invitation from the mayor of Angel Falls to a gala may give away Elisa's former identity as a superheroine.
name: Best Laid Plains

volume.name: Amazonia: The Continuing Adventures of E

description:
Another World - Part 2

After the blackout event in issue one, what's happened to the world? What happened to Katherine and Ben? Where is Mr. Holly after the burning of Vatican City? Come on in and find out in the long (very long) awaited second issue of American Dark Age.
name: Another World, Part Two

description:
The Legend Begins

Having just discovered his new powers, Will and his friends Deltwin and Yaronath, begin the quest to find the Portal Mages of Antispire and hopefully get some answers. Unfortunately getting there will be no walk in the park...
name: The Legend Begins

description: Run for cover, the Menaces are back in action! There's a BONE-anza of Menacing on offer after a rare dinosaur bone goes missing and Dennis's best pal, Gnasher, gets the blame! Can Dennis find Gnasher and get the bone back to the museum, or are the Menace team going to end up like everything else in the museum..? HISTORY! Menaces Unite!
name: Tanks For the Menacing!

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
War Games

The sci-fi, action/adventure contained within includes the following ingredients...

A crashlanding on a desolate ice world.

An impossibly high-class shindig.

Dignitaries. Celebrities. Policy makers. Captains of industry. Architects of conflict. And a sociopathic albino selling stolen military-grade super-science secrets to the highest bidder.

Harsh language.

Occasional violence.

Party crashers. More party crashers.

Threats, both idle and immediate.

And an escape?

BIG HITTERS #3. Hop aboard. It's gonna be a wild ride!
name: War Games

description:
Raiders Of The Abyss

In a dystopian future where the souls of men are bartered and fed upon by a society of resurrected undead. A continuation from Boundead Issue #1.
name: Raiders Of The Abyss

description:
Chance

Issue #7 has four varied stories on a theme of "Chance." Three stories from Josh Kramer: camouflage history, Alaskan marijuana laws, and space debris. Strong brief entries from Emma Woodbury Rand on a mysterious rum runner during prohibition, and from Craig Schaffer on an unusual building in Reading, Pennsylvania.
name: Chance

description: Sister Long and her friends at the MTC learn the importance of dedication and a good sense of humor as they tackle Japanese and the routine of missionary life.
name: Month 2: March

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description: Attending a punk gig brings out a different side of Chopstick, as Mewt guides him deeper into the night. Meanwhile Tracy finds herself caught between a rock and a hard place: a gang of vengeful skinheads and the unpredictable Jugga.

Serialized from the pages of Dungeon Quest Book Three by Joe Daly, we join Millenium Boy, Millenium Boy, Steve, Nerd Girl and Lash Penis mid-adventure. Steve and Lash's bodies go through some EPIC transformations during this fight sequence outside the lair where Nerd Girl is being kept prisoner.

Making Up is Hard to Do

The stunning conclusion to the Ul'Thax Proposal storyline that started in January leaves Captain Heroic and his villainous wife at odds.

Then, in a special bonus section, relive the best moments of the sultry space pirate Captain Scarr.
name: Ul'thax Conclusion: Making Up Is Hard To Do

description: Seyfettin Efendi is ordered to establish an organization to solve mysterious events. Their first case is to investigate a killer who slaughtered female victims and drank their blood in various parts of Istanbul. A secret organization also helps the killer.
name: A Demon Inbetween the Seven Hills Part 4

volume.name: The Exceptional Adventures Of Seyfettin Efendi

description: As Argent and Omega security forces turn the Hex upside down, we learn just how much Vera knows about Omega Corp and the Radix. Plans for what to do next are stalled when Osrick mysteriously disappears.

Now that the terror has started, it must be followed through until the end. No one can survive to tell the tale. With a switch of perspective, the focus is drawn from the hunter to the survivor who will try anything to make it through the night.
Superman and Wonder Woman each visit Alpert’s Eternity Institute, but they don’t get the same warm welcome. And in Gotham, Batman joins the fight for humanity’s future!
name: Genesis - Part 3 of 9

description: Amidst the chaos arrives Havik's champion...Raiden?! But how can this be?
name: Blood Island Chapter 28: Reiko's Blood Reigns

description:
Stampede

Agent discovers that two groups are pursing her and the young girl she has just saved.
name: Stampede

description:
Time

A time travel adventure involving a microwave that not only has the ability to visit different moments in history, but also transform its travellers into fitting relics! It's a random one.
name: Time

description: 50+ pages about xenophobia: 4 powerful stories & 2 terrific illustrations from the best new talent in comics. Plus unique interviews with Fran Syass and Giles Crawford.
name: Volume Three: Xenophobia

description:
...Now That I'm Alone

Coil uses his ill-gotten goods to advance his criminal career. While Icicle, having survived his betrayal, must decide how, and why, to continue living.
name: ...Now That I'm Alone

description:
Necromancer's Lair

Red and her group are received as guests by The Necromancer, but what awaits them in his desert cave? It's a gamble to seek help from someone they don't know and may not trust, but their situation gives them little choice. If nothing else, perhaps Necromancer's knowledge will give them a better understanding of the events leading to the fall of The Kingdom, and just how dire their current fight for survival may be.
name: Necromancer's Lair

description: As Finn and team reach Dracula's castle, unforeseen agendas within the team and among the vampire elite threaten to complicate the situation.

The Third Man's masterfully executed plan finally comes to fruition as a field trip to Vegas turns into one last chance for the Fogeys to prove their mettle. Will they be found worthy or wanting? Either way, after this, NOTHING will be the same.
A quiet city banquet takes a totally unexpected turn. And who said that heroes don't know how to have fun?

Toronto's next generation of comic creators bring you all-new local stories!

We all share Toronto, but no two of us see it alike. Inside these covers you'll find twenty fresh angles on the city we love, from thirty-three talented creators.

From condo vampires to caped heroes, from thrift-store lifers to the pilots of mighty Toronto-Tron, everyone's got a different perspective. Whether you're looking for icy horror, true tales of weird history, or romance at the end of the world, there's a story in here that will change how you see Toronto.

Back and better than ever, our second volume brings many returning creators, as well as new artists and writers working in comics for the first time.
name: Volume 2

description:

  • Assassination Classroom Ch. 146

name: No. 32 July 20, 2015

description:
The Pony Latitudes

Buccaneers, bounty hunters, and booty! Could this be the end for Obadiah Dirt and The Stranger? This Wee Westerns goes where no other toy western has gone... to sea!
name: The Pony Latitudes

description: Yani gets into a fight with her parents and they call the police on her. Where she goes next is not what she expected. Her ex-boyfriend, Matt, helps Jad understand some of the details of what happened.
name: Book 4

description: Kitty was left heartbroken after her affair with Jake, who was far above her status. After spending their first night together, he suddenly seemed to become a different person, and then married another woman! "I'll never come back to this place," she vowed. Time passes and Kitty makes it big as an actress. However, hearing of her grandmother's death, she returns to her hometown for the first time in 8 years, only to bump into Jake! "You finally came back," he said. Jake, a man who left a deep scar in her heart... But why does her heart flutter when she sees him?
name: Vol. 1

description: Christina is a tanned tomboy who works as a crew member on ships. One day she is suddenly approached by a handsome and mysterious man at a Mediterranean harbor town. Why would he choose to talk to her, when there are so many other beautiful girls? He tells her his name is Luc Henri, and she realizes everyone in town knows him by name. He tells her he will see her again before leaving. A few days later, while working on a ship chartered by a royal family, Christina bumps into Luc again...
name: Vol. 1

description: Why is Jack Tarkenton here? Meg doubts her eyes. Why would he turn up at her husband's funeral of all places? Jack, the son of an affluent family that rivals the Kennedys, spent a passionate night with Meg 5 years ago. From this union, their daughter, Katie, was born. Jack does not know about Katie, and Meg does not intend to tell him. However, now that he's approached Meg, this exceptionally wealthy and handsome man intimidates and overpowers her. Even though she never wants anything to do with him ever again!
name: Vol. 1

description: On a cold, rainy night Lily Morgan waited for the man she loved but he never came. She didn't see Nico Cavelli again, until two years later when she's mistakenly arrested in his country. Finding her in jail isn't the only surprise waiting for Nico. He decides to break off his arranged engagement in order to marry her after finding out she had kept the secret of their son from him. Lily gets to marry the man she fell in love with, but is he the same man he used to be? Is Nico really ready to have a family to love?
name: Vol. 1

description: Kathleen's dream was to be a vocalist. That was until the accident that left her with an injured leg. Despite this, her music teacher, Sister Cecily, takes her to an audition. Kathleen is a classical musician, but the audition is being judged by Morgan Llewellyn, a world-famous musical composer. Kathleen performs as best as she can, but the fiercely masculine and overbearing Morgan coldly tells her that she could never be a star.
name: Vol. 1

description: Terry has been in love with J.B for 7 years. He is a wealthy and powerful playboy, but he took her in when she had nowhere else to go, and was like family to her. She hoped he would reciprocate her love one day...but J.B breaks her heart instead. "Do you think I would ever want you?" he tells her. Distraught, Terry runs out of the house and is involved in a road accident. When she awakes, her memory has reverted to when she was 17... When J.B used to care for her...
name: Vol. 1

description: Welcome to Danbury Department Stores, where you'll find the hottest fashions at low, low prices, and you might even have your choice of suitors! Be careful, as which one you choose will end up running Danbury! Could it be the blond Derek or the raven-haired Stephen that you'd like to ring up as your husband today? With the fate of the company resting on who gets married first, which one would you like to return for your stand-in groom?
name: Vol. 1

description: Alessandra works at an advertisement agency in London, and is married to Cameron Calder, a well-known CEO of a large enterprise. The charismatic Cameron always manages to charm anyone he meets, but when he first meets Alessandra, she treats him coldly. Cameron is fascinated by this "cool lady," and asks her to marry him! But Alessandra doesn't know...that this marriage will bring a seemingly endless suffering...
name: Vol. 1

description: Diana has been specially selected to be the driver for Sheikh Zahir, an Arabic prince, during his visit to England. This is the first time a woman has ever driven for the royal family, so Diana has to be on her best behavior! But perhaps because women drivers are so rare, the beautiful Sheikh Zahir, with his dangerous aura, ignores the sullen looks from his aide and strikes up a conversation with Diana. In the end, Diana can't resist him, and on the very night they meet he steals a kiss from her lips. But he's probably just fooling around...
name: Vol. 1

description: In the mountains of North Carolina lies a mansion named Windsong Place. Ryan, the heir to the mansion, and Sunny, the housekeeper's granddaughter, fall in love and marry. However, Ryan's father, angry at his son's marriage to a girl far below his status, disinherits Ryan and sells off the mansion. Soon after, their marriage deteriorates and Ryan and Sunny go their separate ways... 10 years later, Windsong Place, now a hotel, is being auctioned. Ryan returns to make a bid for the hotel, while Sunny arrives hoping to find work. And there, the two meet again!
name: Vol. 1

description: Businessman Jarrett travels to Canada in order to secure the purchase of a business. There he meets his newly married friend and his wife, and agrees to join them for dinner. He is introduced to a former model, Abbie. Jarrett falls in love at first sight, but her suspicious behavior leads him to assume she is a high-class escort. But her true identity is even more surprising!
name: Vol. 1

description: "Hannah, will you marry me?" The proposal from Ethan, a man she loves, should have been the happiest moment of her life... If the marriage wasn't just a contract. Hannah was hired as a nanny after Ethan's wife passed away, then Ethan asks her to be "a mother to his children." Hannah wants to be loved as a woman, but it seems Ethan cannot forget about his late wife... When will he realize Hannah's true feelings?
name: Vol. 1
